fall apart if you're not there.

16:40.133 --> 16:42.333
- You are the gang.
- [scoffs]

16:42.333 --> 16:45.366
I mean that, Rae. Everyone else
has got too much stuff going on.

16:45.366 --> 16:49.066
You're the most...
you know, normal.

16:49.066 --> 16:52.666
- That's bollocks.
- It's true!

16:52.666 --> 16:54.700
Anyway, you've got to go.
I won't take no for answer.

16:54.700 --> 16:57.400
- Because...
- Because what?

17:27.733 --> 17:28.766
You OK?

17:28.766 --> 17:31.633
- No... I just...
- What's up?

17:32.333 --> 17:34.866
I don't feel very well.

17:34.866 --> 17:37.666
Do you want me to see if my
Dad'll give you a lift home?

17:39.800 --> 17:42.833
<i>[Rae]</i>
<i>Oh, God! No vomitorium.</i>

17:42.833 --> 17:46.400
[dad] You'll like this,
I got really bladdered

17:46.400 --> 17:48.700
at a Status Quo concert once.

18:00.433 --> 18:03.533
<i>[Rae]</i>
<i>Round two to Chloe.</i>

18:05.166 --> 18:08.333
<i>[Tix]</i>
<i>Just relax. He's just a boy.</i>

18:08.333 --> 18:11.133
<i>Rae would say something funny.</i>

18:11.133 --> 18:13.833
<i>Maybe I should tell a joke?</i>

18:13.833 --> 18:20.133
<i>No... don't tell any jokes!</i>
<i>Just make conversation.</i>

18:20.133 --> 18:22.700
What do you want to talk about?

18:25.000 --> 18:29.233
Ducks. They are one of
my favorite things, ducks.

18:29.233 --> 18:30.900
I mean, when you
think about a duck.

18:30.900 --> 18:33.766
They're just so chilled out.

18:33.766 --> 18:36.233
They're not chilled out.
I've seen them fight.

18:36.233 --> 18:39.666
Yeah, but once they've done
flapping their wings
and splashing about and stuff

18:39.666 --> 18:43.666
they just go back
to being so... chilled out.

18:45.333 --> 18:46.533
Hey, do you know
what we should do?

18:46.533 --> 18:49.333
- What?
- We should become ducks.

18:49.333 --> 18:51.633
We could go into the pond.

18:53.133 --> 18:55.266
[chuckles]

18:58.233 --> 19:00.766
Danny, no! They'll see you
from the windows.

19:00.766 --> 19:03.100
I fear nothing.

19:08.533 --> 19:09.666
Come on then.

19:12.300 --> 19:14.133
<i>[Tix] Lose control.</i>

19:15.833 --> 19:17.466
<i>Let go.</i>

19:18.300 --> 19:22.233
<i>Lose control, let go.</i>

19:22.233 --> 19:25.933
<i>Lose control, let go.</i>

19:25.933 --> 19:28.500
<i>Lose control, let go.</i>

19:33.800 --> 19:34.833
Come on.

19:34.833 --> 19:37.166
[ducks quacking]

19:43.133 --> 19:45.133
[retching]

19:47.133 --> 19:48.766
Oh, shit.

19:51.400 --> 19:54.300
<i>[Rae]</i>
<i>Fucking pills. Fucking doctors.</i>

19:54.300 --> 19:59.000
<i>How was I supposed to compete</i>
<i>for Finn when I couldn't go</i>
<i>anywhere,</i>

19:59.000 --> 20:01.400
<i>couldn't do anything.</i>

20:06.400 --> 20:10.266
<i>At least there was one adult</i>
<i>on the planet who understood.</i>

20:10.266 --> 20:13.500
It's a load of crap. I'm 16.

20:13.500 --> 20:16.600
Everyone else is going
and she's all like,

20:16.600 --> 20:18.866
"Oh, you can't go
because you're different,

20:18.866 --> 20:23.033
you shouldn't be
exposing yourself
to that kind of situation".

20:23.033 --> 20:25.466
She even used you
as an argument.

20:25.466 --> 20:28.333
"Oh, think of
what Kester would say...".

20:28.333 --> 20:30.133
And what did she think I'd say?

20:30.133 --> 20:33.700
She said you'd think
it was a bad idea.

20:33.700 --> 20:36.766
But she doesn't know about
everything we talk about
in here.

20:36.766 --> 20:42.300
She doesn't know all the work
we've done on me
being brave and confident.

20:42.300 --> 20:45.100
She just reminds me
I'm ill all the time.

20:45.100 --> 20:48.100
I agree with your mum.
I think it's a terrible idea.

20:48.100 --> 20:51.066
[scoffs]
You don't think that.

20:51.066 --> 20:52.933
You're recovering
from a serious illness.

20:52.933 --> 20:56.033
If you'd broken your leg,
would you try and run a marathon
two months later?

20:59.566 --> 21:01.700
Do you still think
I'm a mess then?

21:01.700 --> 21:04.233
I don't think you're a mess.

21:04.233 --> 21:06.133
I think you need to
take care of yourself.

21:06.133 --> 21:09.166
I need to take care of myself?

21:13.200 --> 21:17.633
Who were you arguing with...
last week in the car park?

21:18.300 --> 21:23.300
I saw you. Was it your wife?

21:23.300 --> 21:25.666
How am I supposed to
listen to someone

21:25.666 --> 21:28.400
whose life
is a bigger mess than mine?

21:28.400 --> 21:31.966
What is even the point
of these sessions? Seriously.

21:31.966 --> 21:33.566
To find out
what pushed you over the edge

21:33.566 --> 21:35.233
and to stop it
from happening again.

21:35.233 --> 21:37.233
Oh, you're always
asking questions.

21:37.233 --> 21:39.533
Why did you hurt yourself?
Why did you go crazy?

21:39.533 --> 21:42.766
Sometimes there is no why.
I just did!

21:42.766 --> 21:46.966
And being here and being asked
about it every bloody day

21:46.966 --> 21:48.633
is what's keeping it alive!

21:48.633 --> 21:52.166
- Look, I know this is painful--
- Are you even listening to me?

21:52.933 --> 21:54.766
[sighs]

21:57.833 --> 22:01.900
I was bored. I was lonely.

22:01.900 --> 22:04.600
I had no mates.

22:05.400 --> 22:08.266
Now I'm finally popular...

22:09.500 --> 22:12.166
...and you just want to
make me feel different again.

22:15.866 --> 22:18.033
I don't want to
come here anymore.

22:18.033 --> 22:20.066
[Kester] You're not obliged
to come here, Rae.

22:20.066 --> 22:22.100
But I think
that would be a bad idea.

22:22.100 --> 22:24.966
I think we're making
some real progress here.

22:24.966 --> 22:31.800
What would happen if I just
walked out of that door right
now and never came back?

22:31.800 --> 22:35.566
Aren't you going to try
and say something insightful
to make me stay?

22:36.700 --> 22:38.500
Do you think perhaps...

22:39.666 --> 22:43.266
...your anger is born out of
frustration with yourself?

22:43.266 --> 22:48.866
That you're angry and frustrated
with yourself for being ill?

22:48.866 --> 22:54.033
You see,
that is not something you are
entirely responsible for...

22:54.033 --> 22:56.500
[rock song plays]

22:58.600 --> 23:00.600
[door slams]

23:08.000 --> 23:10.366
[clanging]

23:18.666 --> 23:20.766
[Mum whooping]

23:34.833 --> 23:38.200
I bloody love you, beasty.

23:57.900 --> 24:00.100
[birds tweeting]

24:34.666 --> 24:37.900
<i>[Rae]</i>
<i>Friday, the 23rd of August.</i>

24:37.900 --> 24:40.466
<i>Dear Diary,</i>

24:46.133 --> 24:48.566
<i>Oh, bollocks to it!</i>

24:54.800 --> 24:56.433
Morning.

25:04.833 --> 25:06.400
Morning.

25:11.766 --> 25:13.066
What?

25:46.000 --> 25:48.133
What happened?

25:48.566 --> 25:49.900
What happened?

25:49.900 --> 25:53.966
Someone let
all the birds out the cage.

25:53.966 --> 25:55.233
That's what happened.

25:55.233 --> 25:59.100
Who did? Why would
someone do such a thing?

25:59.100 --> 26:03.900
I don't know.
Maybe you can tell me why
someone would do such a thing?

26:03.900 --> 26:05.566
Oh, my...

26:05.566 --> 26:08.000
Do you wanna tell me
why you did it?

26:08.000 --> 26:10.800
Well,
I didn't know they'd die...

26:10.800 --> 26:13.700
What did you think they'd do?
Fly back to the Bahamas?

26:13.700 --> 26:18.566
Check in at the local RSPB?
Karim is in bits.

26:18.566 --> 26:23.233
He built this because he doesn't
know many people here,
he wanted a project,

26:23.233 --> 26:25.600
something nice
so he didn't feel so trapped.

26:25.600 --> 26:28.266
I did it because
they shouldn't be in a cage.

26:28.266 --> 26:29.533
They're birds,
they are not toys.

26:29.533 --> 26:32.200
No, no, you did it
to get back at me

26:32.200 --> 26:34.900
for not letting you
go to the rave. Didn't you?

26:34.900 --> 26:38.100
Well, is it any wonder
I won't let you go
when you do things like this,

26:38.100 --> 26:40.300
when you behave
like a mental case?

26:40.300 --> 26:44.500
- Don't call me a mental case.
- You know what I meant.

26:44.500 --> 26:47.433
Don't you ever
call me a fucking mental case.

26:47.433 --> 26:50.333
Don't talk to me like that,
Rae, I'm your mum.

26:50.333 --> 26:53.400
I meant you need to start
behaving like an adult

26:53.400 --> 26:55.433
instead of behaving
like a child.

26:55.433 --> 27:02.300
Yeah, well maybe you need to
start behaving like my mum
instead of behaving like a twat.

27:05.900 --> 27:08.000
I'm sorry, Rae.

27:08.966 --> 27:10.700
Save it.

27:25.100 --> 27:27.033
Where are you going?

27:27.033 --> 27:30.500
Dunno. Anywhere.
Away from you. Away from him.

27:30.500 --> 27:36.400
Rae don't go.
Let's talk about this.
I'm really sorry.

27:36.400 --> 27:39.733
Why don't you slap me,
and then we're even.

27:39.733 --> 27:41.966
I don't want to slap you.

27:41.966 --> 27:44.600
I don't even
want to look at you.

27:57.266 --> 28:00.933
<i>[Rae] I'd always known</i>
<i>I'd have to run away</i>
<i>from home at some point.</i>

28:00.933 --> 28:04.266
<i>I'd always planned</i>
<i>that I'd go</i>
<i>and stop at Chloe's.</i>

28:04.266 --> 28:08.633
<i>We'd be like sisters,</i>
<i>I'd have a normal family.</i>

28:11.700 --> 28:14.266
<i>But things change.</i>

28:33.500 --> 28:35.366
[door opens]

28:37.700 --> 28:39.333
There you go.

28:41.266 --> 28:43.700
Tea makes everything alright.

28:46.233 --> 28:48.600
I reckon it'll be alright,
you know, in a couple of days.

28:48.600 --> 28:51.233
When you've both had
some space or whatever.

28:53.366 --> 28:56.833
- Thanks for letting me stop.
- It's alright.

28:56.833 --> 28:59.900
My dad's ironing sheets
for the spare room as we speak.

28:59.900 --> 29:01.433
Oh, please don't
let him do that.

29:01.433 --> 29:03.333
I wouldn't try and stop him.

29:04.400 --> 29:06.266
So, what time's the rave?

29:06.266 --> 29:09.700
Probably set off
in about an hour.
Why, you thinking of coming?

29:09.700 --> 29:15.266
No. No, I'm not. It'd mess up
all the lifts and stuff anyway.

29:15.266 --> 29:18.300
Ni, it wouldn't, bollocks, no.
I'll tell Chloe
to jump in with Chop,

29:18.300 --> 29:20.266
and you can get on
the scooter with me.

29:29.600 --> 29:32.633
<i>[Tix] I can't even</i>
<i>dip my toe in a pond.</i>

29:32.633 --> 29:36.200
<i>I can't even lose control</i>
<i>enough to get my feet wet.</i>

29:36.200 --> 29:37.600
<i>I'll never be normal.</i>

29:37.600 --> 29:39.800
<i>I'll never be able</i>
<i>to talk to Rae about</i>

29:39.800 --> 29:41.866
<i>kissing and flirting and love.</i>

29:41.866 --> 29:43.300
<i>I'll never be like...</i>

29:43.300 --> 29:44.266
Rae?

29:44.266 --> 29:45.666
[Kester clears throat]
It's me.

29:45.666 --> 29:49.200
- What are you doing in here?
- Hiding.

29:49.200 --> 29:54.366
- Why? What you doing in here?
- Hiding.

29:54.366 --> 29:58.400
I thought you'd be getting ready
for your big date with Rae.

29:59.533 --> 30:04.100
I'm not going. Please don't try
and convince me to go.

30:05.700 --> 30:11.000
I once treated a young boy
of about seven-years-old,

30:11.000 --> 30:13.866
he used to pull down on his
testicles whenever he was upset.

30:13.866 --> 30:19.433
I mean really yank down.
It was truly eye-watering
to behold.

30:19.433 --> 30:23.933
Then one day I asked him
a difficult question...

30:23.933 --> 30:26.233
...and he pulled down
so hard upon them

30:26.233 --> 30:28.133
that he had to go to hospital.

30:28.833 --> 30:31.500
That's crazy.

30:31.500 --> 30:33.266
You'd be surprised
what lengths people will go

30:33.266 --> 30:38.533
to not to face what's real
and painful inside them.

30:38.533 --> 30:45.100
But that's what my job is,
I'm essentially a torturer.

30:45.100 --> 30:46.933
This is were you say
I'm not a torturer,

30:46.933 --> 30:48.866
that I'm actually quite lovely.

30:48.866 --> 30:52.866
My methods of torture
are asking you to trust people,

30:52.866 --> 30:55.000
asking you to lose control.

30:55.000 --> 30:59.266
But if I'd been treated the way
you'd been treated by people,

31:00.366 --> 31:02.000
I'd want to sit in a toilet

31:02.000 --> 31:04.300
and hide from the rest
of the world as well.

31:04.300 --> 31:07.266
You are sitting in a toilet.

31:08.933 --> 31:10.233
It's really quite nice,
actually.

31:10.233 --> 31:12.633
I can see why you
and Rae hang out here.

31:13.666 --> 31:18.133
I do trust people, you know?
I trust, Rae.

31:18.133 --> 31:21.833
Well, then maybe you should
have dinner with her.

31:21.833 --> 31:25.366
[slow-tempo music plays]

32:19.100 --> 32:22.000
- Finn!
- [yelling]

33:16.066 --> 33:17.100
[giggling]

33:17.100 --> 33:18.833
You alright?

33:18.833 --> 33:22.933
Listen. Try and have
a good night. Enjoy yourself.

33:22.933 --> 33:24.633
Uh, what's going on
with you two?

33:24.633 --> 33:27.600
- What do you mean?
- You look like a couple.

33:27.600 --> 33:31.100
Come on, Chloe. We look like
a better couple than they do.

33:34.600 --> 33:36.266
[whooping]

33:39.166 --> 33:41.600
[house music plays]

33:53.066 --> 33:55.566
[indistinct chatter]

34:01.933 --> 34:03.366
Uh, no way.

34:03.366 --> 34:05.133
- What are you doing?
- Taking a pill.

34:05.133 --> 34:07.900
[Chop] No, you hate drugs.
You don't take drugs.

34:07.900 --> 34:09.233
You said
there's one for everyone.

34:09.233 --> 34:10.533
Well, not for you,
you're different.

34:10.533 --> 34:14.033
- Why am I different?
- Rae? Are you in?

34:15.633 --> 34:18.766
Ladies and gentlemen,
start your engines.

34:23.500 --> 34:25.533
<i>[Tix] What's the point</i>
<i>in keeping a diary</i>

34:25.533 --> 34:27.900
<i>when you're too</i>
<i>scared to ever do anything?</i>

34:27.900 --> 34:32.866
<i>When you life is boring,</i>
<i>when the only things</i>
<i>you know are</i>

34:32.866 --> 34:38.166
<i>how many calories things</i>
<i>contain and how to lose them.</i>

34:38.166 --> 34:40.466
[rock song plays]

34:53.900 --> 34:56.600
[crowd noise]

35:09.100 --> 35:11.633
Oh, my God, Rae, I can't believe
you dropped a pill!

35:11.633 --> 35:15.766
Yeah, well, you're the one
who told me to chill.

35:15.766 --> 35:19.366
So, how's things
going with Finn?

35:19.366 --> 35:22.700
OK... Are you staying
at his tonight?

35:22.700 --> 35:25.733
Yeah... but it's a long story.

35:25.733 --> 35:26.933
But, do you like him?

35:26.933 --> 35:31.666
What, Finn?
No, we're just best mates.

35:31.666 --> 35:34.266
I really want to kiss him
but I dunno...

35:35.000 --> 35:36.633
I think he likes someone else.

35:36.633 --> 35:38.666
Oh... Who?

35:38.666 --> 35:41.933
I'm not too sure.
Has he said anything to you?

35:41.933 --> 35:45.166
- No.
- Maybe I won't try then.

35:47.333 --> 35:51.366
Whoo!
Archie, come here!

35:53.300 --> 35:55.266
Yeah!

35:58.133 --> 36:00.966
If you were a bloke
I'd shag your lights out.

36:00.966 --> 36:05.200
Yeah? And if I was a bloke
I'd let you.

36:07.200 --> 36:08.633
I fucking love you, Rae.

36:08.633 --> 36:11.666
Promise me we'll hang out
next year at college, yeah.

36:18.633 --> 36:20.200
Whoo!

36:47.066 --> 36:50.400
[music continues]
[whistle blowing]

36:52.866 --> 36:56.400
- I know you.
- Everyone knows me.

36:56.400 --> 36:59.066
You've got the fucking moves,
girl.

36:59.066 --> 37:02.966
I love it. I love to dance.
I just love it.

37:02.966 --> 37:05.233
Right, come dance with me.

37:06.733 --> 37:08.766
You got anything?

37:15.566 --> 37:20.133
I'm single. Are you?
Are you here with someone?

37:20.933 --> 37:23.900
No, I'm not single.

37:23.900 --> 37:25.566
You can be single if you want.

37:34.433 --> 37:35.900
[both chuckle]

37:35.900 --> 37:38.366
Rae! Rae!
Come here, come here...

37:38.366 --> 37:40.200
What you doing?
I was talking to her.

37:40.200 --> 37:41.266
I'll bring her back in a second.

37:41.266 --> 37:43.133
I just need to
borrow her a minute.

37:53.333 --> 37:54.433
What are you doing
with knobhead?

37:54.433 --> 37:56.400
What are you doing with Kendo?

37:56.400 --> 37:59.966
- Are you crying?
- I fucking love her.

37:59.966 --> 38:02.866
- Who?
- Izzy! I fucking love her.

38:02.866 --> 38:05.566
Whoa!
Why are you telling me this?

38:05.566 --> 38:09.533
Because you're the Daddy.
You know everything.
Tell me what to do.

38:09.533 --> 38:13.066
Oh! Tell her.

38:13.066 --> 38:18.033
Just go over there
and tell her and be happy. Yeah?

38:19.433 --> 38:20.566
Yeah.

38:29.933 --> 38:32.666
Bloody hell.

38:33.800 --> 38:36.966
Come on.

38:36.966 --> 38:39.133
Chop!

38:40.433 --> 38:42.400
Hey, Barney, have you seen Chop?

38:42.400 --> 38:43.600
[scoffs]

38:43.600 --> 38:46.000
Uh, Chop!

38:49.366 --> 38:50.366
Chop!

38:50.366 --> 38:53.900
[exhales]
Jesus, Rae. I'm so fucked.

38:53.900 --> 38:56.766
Yeah, me too.

38:56.766 --> 39:00.566
Mm... Um...
Where the fuck is he?

39:01.400 --> 39:03.433
Boy's a constant flight risk.

39:03.433 --> 39:08.333
Alright, just leave it, right.
He'll come back when he's ready.

39:08.333 --> 39:11.233
And... I need another drink.

39:11.233 --> 39:13.833
- So, come on...
- So, come on.

39:13.833 --> 39:18.333
- Let's go...
Why are you laughing?
- [laughing]

39:22.066 --> 39:24.533
[house music plays]

39:26.866 --> 39:31.066
- No way, I'll chunder.
- Oh, pussy.

39:34.733 --> 39:38.533
Alright, I need to kiss him
tonight, babes.

39:38.533 --> 39:42.566
- Who?
- I need to kiss him.

39:42.566 --> 39:46.000
I need to tell him.
He needs to know.

39:46.000 --> 39:47.666
What you talking about?
You're fucked.

39:47.666 --> 39:52.433
No... I'm alright.
I need to kiss him,

39:52.433 --> 39:55.633
and I need to tell him,
he needs to know!

39:57.933 --> 39:59.600
Finn?

39:59.600 --> 40:01.633
- Finn?
- Piss off.

40:02.500 --> 40:05.600
Finn! Finn!

40:10.566 --> 40:12.100
Finn?

40:16.666 --> 40:18.600
No...

40:22.366 --> 40:24.666
- No!
- Rae! Rae!

40:29.000 --> 40:30.366
Rae!

40:30.900 --> 40:32.433
Rae!

40:38.100 --> 40:39.533
[Mum] Rae?

40:43.533 --> 40:45.500
[giggling]

40:56.033 --> 40:58.300
[birds chirping]

41:07.533 --> 41:09.266
[blows raspberry]

41:33.633 --> 41:35.433
[sighs]

41:39.300 --> 41:43.633
- How you feeling?
- Like twice boiled shit.

41:43.633 --> 41:47.000
Can you remember
anything from last night?

41:49.833 --> 41:51.133
A little.

41:51.133 --> 41:53.800
I can't remember a thing.

41:55.266 --> 41:57.266
You're stopping at Finn's right?

41:58.200 --> 42:00.233
No, just take me home.

42:00.233 --> 42:02.233
What about your mum?

42:06.200 --> 42:08.800
[soft rock song plays]

42:29.900 --> 42:31.733
What the fuck?

42:31.733 --> 42:33.633
Karim...

42:40.266 --> 42:41.933
You sure you wanna go home?

42:41.933 --> 42:43.633
Yeah.

43:21.166 --> 43:22.800
<i>[Rae]</i>
<i>Dear Diary,</i>

43:22.800 --> 43:27.166
<i>If tea makes everything better,</i>
<i>I need an ocean of it.</i>

43:27.166 --> 43:30.033
<i>I need all the tea in China.</i>

43:30.033 --> 43:33.333
<i>Sorry, I haven't written</i>
<i>for a while but...</i>

43:33.333 --> 43:36.300
<i>Well, what do you expect?</i>

43:36.300 --> 43:41.333
<i>I'm unreliable,</i>
<i>I'm a mess, I'm mental.</i>

43:48.500 --> 43:50.466
Hello, Mandela.

43:57.833 --> 44:00.266
[phone ringing]

44:09.533 --> 44:10.466
Hello.

44:10.466 --> 44:12.866
<i>[Kester]</i>
<i>Rae? It's Kester.</i>

44:12.866 --> 44:14.300
<i>Look... it's about Tix.</i>

44:14.300 --> 44:17.200
Oh, shit!
The meal, I missed it.

44:17.200 --> 44:19.133
Is she there?
Can I speak to her?

44:19.133 --> 44:23.833
<i>- No, it's not... she...</i>
- What?

44:23.833 --> 44:26.600
<i>She collapsed this morning.</i>

44:27.133 --> 44:28.700
Is it serious?

44:28.700 --> 44:31.566
<i>How quickly can you</i>
<i>get to the hospital?</i>
